The paper deals with optimization problems and their approximations, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of computer science related to algorithms and complexity. Specifically, the paper focuses on Quadratic Programming (QP) problems, which are often studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of semidefinite programming techniques suggests a connection to cs.CG (Computational Geometry), while the mention of eigenvalue relaxations and distributions on instances suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
